Package: sstp-server
Architecture: linux-any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, adduser, udev
Recommends: sstp-server-dkms (= ${source:Version})
Suggests: freeradius
Description: Microsoft SSTP VPN server (userspace daemon)
 sstp-server is a high-performance Linux SSTP (Secure Socket Tunneling
 Protocol, [MS-SSTP]) server. It terminates SSTP/TLS from Windows clients,
 runs the PPP control plane in-process, and forwards IP through the Linux
 kernel via /dev/ppp.
 .
 Authentication is delegated to RADIUS (PAP, CHAP, MS-CHAPv2, EAP). IP
 address assignment is RADIUS-driven (Framed-IP-Address, Framed-Route,
 MS-Primary-DNS-Server, ...).
 .
 This package contains the userspace daemon and a systemd service unit.
 Also included is sstp-server-cli, an interactive admin REPL that
 connects to the daemon's control socket (see sstp-server(8) for the
 supported commands: `show info`, `show stat`, `show sess`, `disable
 session`, `shutdown`).
 .
 For the optional in-kernel fast path (kTLS + ppp_channel), install the
 companion sstp-server-dkms package.

Package: sstp-server-dkms
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, dkms (>= 2.1.0.0)
Recommends: linux-headers-generic | linux-headers-amd64 | linux-headers-arm64
Description: SSTP kernel module (DKMS sources)
 In-tree DKMS sources for the sstp kernel module used by sstp-server's
 kernel fast path. Once loaded, the module registers a ppp_channel
 against an SSTP-attached, kTLS-equipped TCP socket so the steady-state
 data path (kTLS decrypt -> SSTP demux -> ppp_input) runs entirely in
 kernel context.
 .
 Requires kernel 6.12 or newer with CONFIG_PPP=m and matching
 linux-headers installed.
